race.comment: WELL TIMED (1) was most impressive first-up then disappointed under a big weight at Randwick last start over this distance. Burdened with 62.5kgs today but does drop back to midweek company and should be at peak fitness. Worth another chance. SILVANITO (9) turned in an even effort to finish fifth in the same race as WELL TIMED at Randwick last time out. Not a noted second-up performer so that effort is worth overlooking. The winner of two from four when third up so he has a nice sense of timing. SOSINO (4) tired late when returning from 13 months in the paddock last start at Warwick Farm. Import who was Gr 3 placed in France. No surprise if he improved sharply and tested this line-up. PEACE OFFICER (6) did his best work late when runner-up over 1300m at Warwick Farm recently. That was his first appearance in five months so there is improvement to come. HIGH BLUE SEA (3) goes well for Tim Clark who is back aboard. Should be thereabouts.
